headline: Assessing Celestica (TSX:CLS) Valuation After Goldman Sachs Adds It to Its Conviction List
summary: Celestica (TSX:CLS) has jumped back onto investors radar after Goldman Sachs added the stock to its Conviction List, citing its edge in data center and AI focused hardware manufacturing. See our latest analysis for Celestica. That call out from Goldman Sachs comes on top of a powerful run, with Celestica delivering a 253 percent year to date share price return and a 1 year total shareholder return near 280 percent, signalling strong, still building momentum.
